The paper deals with distributed detection over noisy networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and systems and control theory (cs.SY). The use of time-varying weight sequences and communication payoff thresholds suggests a focus on optimization and machine learning (cs.MA) techniques. The paper also discusses numerical examples, indicating a potential focus on networked systems (cs.NI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
